Wash and dry produce. Dice @tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and @chili powder{1%pinch} (you'll use the rest later). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Once veggies are done, heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @tofu{1}, @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and remaining @chili powder{1%teaspoon}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and a splash of water; cook until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with pork and veggies. Drizzle with crema. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and pico de gallo. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and any remaining lime wedges on the side.